From: Eli Cohen <eli@dev.mellanox.co.il>
Date: Tue, 2 Dec 2014 12:26:13 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 117/129] net/mlx5_core: Fix command queue size enforcement
Git-commit: 2d446d18aa09f16aef9e34774c4fcbc8a84a923e
Patch-mainline: v3.19-rc1
References: bnc#905015 fate#317531

Command queue descriptor page size is 4KB and not the page size used by the
kernel.

Signed-off-by: Eli Cohen <eli@mellanox.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>

Signed-off-by: Hadar Hen Zion <hadarh@mellanox.com>
Acked-by: John Jolly <jjolly@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/cmd.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/cmd.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/cmd.c
index 0ee0979..b51a0ed 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/cmd.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/cmd.c
@@ -1372,7 +1372,7 @@ int mlx5_cmd_init(struct mlx5_core_dev *dev)
 		goto err_map;
 	}
 
-	if (cmd->log_sz + cmd->log_stride > PAGE_SHIFT) {
+	if (cmd->log_sz + cmd->log_stride > MLX5_ADAPTER_PAGE_SHIFT) {
 		dev_err(&dev->pdev->dev, "command queue size overflow\n");
 		err = -EINVAL;
 		goto err_map;
